{ Not so surprisingly the only move.  10...Qd7  would invite  11.Ne5!  Qc7  12.Qa4+±  And Black is forced to break castling since after  12...Nbd7  we have  13.Nb5! }
11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Nxd5 exd5 13. O-O O-O 14. dxc5 bxc5 15. Rac1 Qd6 16. Qa3
{ Putting more pressure on the c5-pawn and threatening d4 next. } 16... Nd7 17.
d4 { Mission accomplished. } 17... Rfc8 18. Rc3
{ Threatening Rfc1 to put further pressure on the c5-pawn. A more in-depth analysis is provided here. }
