bxc5
{ 21...Bxc5??  Huge mistake. White is completely winning now.  22.Rd1!+-  White has too many threats.   1@@EndBracket@@ Nf6-Rd7   2@@EndBracket@@ Qf6-Ng7   3@@EndBracket@@ Qf6-Rd8. One of them will ensure a win in this position. }
22. Nf6+ Bxf6 23. Qxf6
{ The position should objectively be defendable for Black, but then again White has tremendous activity, combined with Black's awkwardly placed king and rook, providing many practical chances. The game may continue  23...Qxa2  24.Rd1  Qa5  25.e4  fxe4  26.Qe5  Qb6  27.Qxe4  and, once again, the position is equal - but White still maintains a practical chance thanks to Black's uncoordinated pieces. }
