{ Threatening both Rxb4 and Ne6+. } 16... Nh5
{ 16...Nc6?  17.Ne6+  Bxe6  18.Bxe6  Nxe5  19.Bxe5±  Gives White a substantial advantage in the endgame thanks to the dominating bishops. }
17. Rxb4 Nxf4 18. Ned7+ Kxf7 19. Rxf4+ Bf6 20. Nb6
{ Followed by Ke2-Rc1 and White has a fantastic position. } *

