7... Qc3
{ The most popular move, and rightfully so. This is the best response for Black, as it does not allow White to play c2-c4. }
8. Bb5 { We continue with our normal plan. } 8... Qxc5
{ These types of moves are generally considered to be bad. But regardless it is important to know how to correctly punish them! }
9. O-O { Development is complete, White is ready to throw c4! } 9... a6
{ The most popular move, although it makes little sense since Black is only delaying their development further. }
10. Bxc6+ Qxc6 11. c4 Bg4
{ Stopping Ne5, for now.  11...e6  Allows  12.Ne5  Qc5  13.Qa4++-  Followed by Rfc1. }
