Bg7 { This is another 'logical' move. } 21. Re1+
{ Forcing the bishop on d7 to move. } 21... Be6 22. Bxg7 dxc5
{ 22...Rxg7  loses to  23.Rxe6!+- } 23. Be5
{ We reach a classic endgame where the material is equal, but the position is nearly winning for White. The reason is simply: active pieces. White's bishop is undeniably superior to its opponent. The rook on b7 is a monster. The other rook on e1 is also active. }
