Re3 { Threatening Bxh7+. } 17... g6 18. c3 { Protecting the knight on d4. }
18... Qc7
{ 18...Bb7  is quite careless.  19.Qg4!+-  With a winning attack. White can continue with Rh3 next. }
19. h4 Nc5 20. Bh6 Re8 21. h5
{ White's attack is getting more dangerous with every move. Black's king does not seem to have many defenders, and this is a huge problem. }
