1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Nbd2 Bf5
{ It is natural for Black to get the bishop out before playing ...e6, another way to do this is  5...Bg4  which will be analyzed next. }
6. Bb5
{ Logical and active. The idea is to pose problems along the a4-e8 diagonal with ideas like c4-Ne5. }
