Nxc5 Nxf4 16. exf4 Qd4 17. Ncb3 Qxf4 18. Qf3 Qxg5+ 19. Qg3
{ And White is a piece up. It's true that Black has 3 pawns, which equates to the same number of points, however, the piece undoubtedly takes the preference. }
