15... dxe4 16. Qe2 { No time to waste! } 16... Qxd4 17. O-O
{ A little counterintuitive, but it works. It's important to not confuse the move order. For example, if White plays @@StartFEN@@2rqkb1r/p5p1/2p1p1p1/6Pp/3PpB1P/8/PPP2P2/R2QK2R w KQk - 0 16@@EndFEN@@  16.O-O  Black is close to winning after  16...Bd6! }
17... Bc5 18. Rad1
