6. dxc5 { Free pawns are always welcome. } 6... Nxf4 7. exf4 g6 8. c3 Bg7 9.
Bb5 O-O 10. Bxc6
{ This is the only time we will take on c6. And I will explain why: going for the natural  10.O-O  is not recommended because of  10...d4!  which immediately equalizes the position. }
