{ Note that this move is possible now since the queen on a3 does a good job of protecting the a6-square. }
13. Rb3 Qa5 14. Rab1 { Getting the other rook into play. } 14... Be7
{ 14...Qxa2??  Makes no sense here as Black has already played ...Qa5 and wasted a tempo.  15.Bxc6+  bxc6  16.Rb8+-  with an easy finish. }
15. Bxc6+ bxc6 16. Rb7
{ An extremely precise prophylactic move aimed against O-O. White is also threatening the deadly Rxe7+. }
16... Qa3 { Protecting the e7-bishop, preparing to castle next. } 17. g4
{ Launching a kingside attack since Black will castle inevitably. } 17... Bg6
18. R1b3
{ Weakening the queen's control over the e7-bishop.  18.h4?  is not recommended in this case since after  18...O-O  19.h5  Bxc2  20.R1b2  Black has a pretty intermezzo.  20...Rc7!  21.Rxc7  Qxb2  22.Rxe7  Qb4⩱  And since Black is not losing material and the king is more or less safe, Black holds an advantage. }
18... Qxa2 19. h4
{ Increasing the pressure in Black's camp. Threatening h5 next.   19.Rxe7+  is another interesting option that can be investigated further.  19...Kxe7  20.Rb7+  Kf8  21.h4⩲  And Black will face serious practical problems due to the unsafe king, lack of development and coordination of pieces. }
19... Qa4
{ 19...Bxc2??  Loses the game immediately after  20.Rxe7+  Kxe7  21.Rb7+  Ke8  22.Nxf7+-  Black's position has fallen apart. }
20. c4 { Blocking the queens view. Once again, we are threatening h5. } 20...
dxc4 21. Nexc4
{ 21.Ndxc4?  Seems like the logical capture, but the problem is that now the b3-rook is hanging and Rxe7 is not possible anymore, which allows Black to castle.  21...O-O∓ }
21... Qa1+ 22. Nf1 Qd4
{ Centralising the queen and stopping the deadly Bd6 idea. } 23. Be5 Qe4
{ Blunders away the game after White's natural reply. } 24. Nfe3
{ It's not everyday we see a queen getting trapped by a pawn in the center of the board! }
24... Bc5 25. Nd6+ Bxd6 26. Bxd6
{ White is completely winning, since Black will never be able to castle. White should go Re7+ in the next move to make sure Black's castling is ruptured. }
