g3 Qc7 12. Nd4+ Kd8 13. Nxf5 exf5
{ In the aforementioned game, White went for  14.cxd5  which allowed  14...Qa5  followed by 15... Bb4. This is a small inaccuracy. White should instead focus on developing the king first. }
14. O-O { The pawn isn't going anywhere. } 14... a6 15. Ba4 Rc8 16. Rc1
{ I do not particularly like taking on d5 just yet, since Black can form a blockade via ...Bd6 and use the d5-pawn as a shield to protect the king. }
16... Bd6 17. Re1
{ White maintains a strong initiative due to Black's exposed and undeveloped king. I should mention again that White should refrain from taking cxd5 in this position and instead go for c5 followed by b4 perhaps. }
