Qh5 Rdd1 { Threatening mate in one. } 29. Bf4 Be7
{ Please note that had the pawn been on h4 in this case, White would be in some trouble because of ...Rh1+ followed by ...Bxh4+ threat. }
30. Ne3 { However, in this case - we have nothing to worry about. } *

