Nxg6
{ 15...fxg6  might seem obvious at first since Black is opening up the f-file. However, Black also created weaknesses on e6 and g6, which we can now exploit.  16.Ne2  Rhf8  17.Nf4  Rf7  18.Bh3  Nf8  19.Kb1⩲  Black's pieces are paralyzed on the kingside. If Black decides to go ...Nf5 then we will exchange it with no hesitation. The knight on f4 does a great job of keeping the pressure on e6 and g6. }
16. Na4 Qc6 17. b3
{ Protecting the knight and creating space on the queenside. } 17... Ne7 18.
Kb1
{ Hinting at c4-ideas in the future. The position is closed, only White has a breakthrough possible in this position. }
