13. Kf2 Re8 14. Ng3 exd4 { This is perhaps the best moment for this capture. }
15. Qxd4 Be6 16. Bxe6
{ 16.Qf4  is not working in this case because of  16...Nbd5!  Since after  17.Bxd5  Nxd5  18.Nxd5  Black has a clever intermezzo,  18...Qd2+  which equalizes the position. }
16... Rxe6 17. Nf5
{ And the position is clearly better. The active placement of the White knight on f5 will continue to pose practical problems for a long time, Black could always push ...g6, but it will weaken the h7-pawn which can be attacked via doubling the rooks on the h-file. The extra open file is perhaps the single biggest reason for why this position is better for White. }
