{ I like this move since it avoids the exchange of the dark bishops. Once we have castled, Black would be inclined to take on g3 since there is no attack along the h-file. }
9... Qe7 10. O-O c5 { Is not effective here either. } 11. Bh4
{ And once again, taking on d4 is not an option since we can recapture with the queen. It is quite difficult for Black to develop the b8-knight without rupturing the kingside, and White on the other hand poses a dangerous threat of Bf3. }
