4. Qd3
{ Extremely important. White aims to reroute the queen to either b3 or b5 to attack the b7-pawn. In this position, two moves make sense -  4...c6  and  4...e6  . }
4... e6 { The bold response. Black is not afraid of losing the pawn on b7. } 5.
Qb5+ Nbd7 6. Qxb7 Rb8 7. Qxa7
{ And now if Black wants to have any kind of compensation, Black needs a breakthrough immediately. }
7... e5 8. Bxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Ne4
{ 9...Rxb2??  is not as dangerous in this case.  10.exf6  Bb4+  11.Nd2+- } 10.
Nd2 Rxb2 { The only challenging move. } 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. a3
