13. Qxc7
{ And it seems like White can develop via Be2 next. But Black has one last trick. }
13... Ra2 { The idea is to repeat moves with Rb1-Rb2, Ra1-Ra2. } 14. Qb8+ Ke7
15. Rb1
{ Intending Qc7+ and stopping ...Rb2. A more in-depth analysis of this line is provided here. }
