{ Simple waiting move. Black has no threats, so we don't need to rush. } 15...
g6 16. Qb3
{ Putting pressure on the b7-pawn. Of course, taking is not possible right now, but a smart person once said 'Threat is better than execution'. White should remember that the position will remain slightly better as long as Black is not able to play ...c5 successfully, which is not happening anytime soon. White should probably try to reroute the knights to c5 and f4 respectively to keep the tension on both sides of the board. Once this is done, an idea like Rac1-Nc5 will pose long term problems for Black. }
