{ The idea behind this move is similar to  3...Bg4  .  Black intends to get the bishop out before playing ...e6. Another important note is that unlike the line with 3... c6, Black has smartly kept the pawn on c7 to push ...c5 once the development is complete.  For a long time, I tried to make @@StartFEN@@rn1qkb1r/ppp1pppp/5n2/3p1b2/3P1B2/4P3/PPP2PPP/RN1QKBNR w KQkq - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  4.c4  work here but I did not like the lines with  4...e6  5.Nc3  Bb4!?  and even though this is played regularly at the top level, I believe I have found something much better. }
