c4 Be7 11. Ne5 { Restricting Black from castling. } 11... Bxb5
{ 11...O-O  Will allow White to simplify through a bunch of exchanges and achieve a clearly better position.  12.Nxd7  Nfxd7  13.Bxd7  Nxd7  14.Rxb7  Qd8  15.cxd5  exd5  16.Qa4  Attacking the d7-knight.  16...Nb6  17.Qa3±  keeping pressure on the c5 and a7-pawn. The a7-pawn should fall soon. }
12. Rxb5 Qa6 { Protecting the b7-pawn. } 13. Qb3 b6 14. dxc5 Bxc5
{ 14...O-O  will give White a dangerous pawn after  15.c6⩲  And the c6-pawn rules the position. }
15. cxd5 Nxd5 { 15...exd5  allows  16.Bg5+- } 16. Ne4 O-O 17. Nxc5 bxc5 18.
Rxc5
{ And White retains a better position thanks to piece activity. The b8-knight will struggle to develop, the awkward placement of the Black queen does not help either since the a6-square is blocked. }
