{ I will refer to my note a bit earlier, as you will see, capturing the d7-knight when only the queen can recapture is thematic in these positions. }
13... Qxd7 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Bxe4 dxe4 16. Ne5
{ And White retains a somewhat good knight vs bad bishop situation. The position is objectively equal, but White has ideas of kingside attack with Rg3-Rh3-Qh5. I also like the idea of just pushing h4 and trading the queens as Black's exposed pawn on e4 could pressured in the endgame. }
