{ Simple developing move, we should now keep the threat of c3-c4 in mind. }
11... Bb7
{ The bishop has moved from c8 and only the queen is protecting the knight on d7, this could only mean one thing... }
12. Nxd7 { Correct! } 12... Qxd7 13. Ne5 Qe7
{ 13...Qc7  14.Qg4  Threatening to go f3 next and continue the attack. If Black pushes ...f5 then we can just move with Qh4 and continue with the original plan of f3 and maybe even break the kingside with g2-g4! }
14. f3 { Kicking the knight away. } 14... Nf6 15. Bg5
{ Pinning the knight and threatening Ng4 next, Black is forced to rupture the kingside, and White can soon start the attack. }
