Nd6
{ Only move.  17...Nf6  may seem logical at first, but after  18.g4  fxg4  19.fxg4  Black’s knight on f6 is misplaced and allows to expand on the kingside further via g5 and h4.   17...g5?!  Simply allows for  18.fxe4  fxe4  19.Be2  gxf4  20.Rxf4  and Black’s kingside is vulnerable. White can go for Raf1-Rg4+ ideas soon. }
18. g4 { Can be employed regardless. } 18... a5 19. gxf5 exf5 20. Bb1
{ Prophylactic move aimed against ...c4. If Black plays c4 anyways, we can respond with e4! If Black keeps the pawn on c5, the idea of dxc5-Rd1 seems great. White's monster knight and the London bishop will make sure that your opponent will not be feeling comfortable for a long time. }
