{ I also enjoyed analysing this, although I would not recommend this for more than one game. }
12... dxe4 13. Nxf7 Bxf4
{ 13...Kxf7??  This is the reason why I recommended the variation.  14.Ng5+  Ke7  15.Qh5  Rf8  16.Qxh7+-  with a completely winning position. }
14. Nxd8 exf3 15. exf4 fxg2 16. Re1 Qxd8 17. dxc5 Bb7
{ Protecting the g2-pawn. } 18. cxb6 axb6 19. Rxe6
{ With equality, although I must admit - this position is a lot less pleasant to play in comparison to the other alternative. }
