{ If not for this move, I fail to see the difference between ...Bd6 and ...Be7. This is the most popular move so far in this position. }
9. dxe5 Ne8 { Is also possible. } 10. Qh5 f5
{ 10...g6?!  can be met with  11.Qh6!+-  with the idea of Nf3-Ng5. } 11. Nf3
{ Bringing the knight into action and preparing for g4 next. White is clearly better. }
