9. dxe5 Nd7 10. h4
{ Preparing for Bxh7+ ideas. Let's face it, a London course is incomplete without the greek gift! }
10... f5 { Logical response. } 11. g4
{ Breaking Black's pawn chain and launching a very dangerous kingside attack. }
11... Qc7 12. Nf3
{ Defending the e5-pawn. Do not rush with  12.gxf5?  since it allows  12...Nxe5  and Black manages to escape. }
12... fxg4
{ I don't see any useful moves for Black, so I went with this to show the idea of Nf3. }
13. Ng5 Bxg5
{ Only move.  13...Nxe5  allows  14.Bxh7+  Kh8  15.Bxe5  Qxe5  16.Qxg4+-  with a completely winning position. }
14. hxg5 g6 { Protecting h7. } 15. Qxg4 Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Qxe5 17. Rh6
{ Only move to win! White's idea is to go Qh4 followed by O-O-O. } 17... Qg7
18. Qh4
{ With Bxg6 next. Black's kingside is destroyed and White is completely winning. }
