8... Re8
{ Black obviously wants to push ...e5. It is important that we do not allow this. }
9. Ne5 Qc7 10. f4 Ne7 11. Bh4
{ Going with the same idea. The difference now is that Black's knight on e7 can hop on to g6 to defend the position. }
11... Ng6 12. Bg5
{ Sneaky move. We will delay Bxf6 for now and focus on kicking this knight away with h4-h5. }
12... cxd4
{ 12...Be7  has been tried before, but White can just attack with  13.h4+-  With ideas of Qf3-h5-h6. The position should be completely winning. }
13. cxd4 Ne4
{ This is the best move of the computer, and it drops the pawn - this just goes to show how bad Black's position really is. }
14. Bxe4 dxe4 15. Nxe4 { With a clearly better position. } 15... Bb4+
{ I felt that this move is important to know since White can retain the advantage with only one move here. }
16. Kf2
{ With a completely winning position. White's idea is to go Rc1-Qf3 next. Not  16.Ke2  because of  16...b6!  And Black generates some counterplay on the queenside. }
