14... Kxg7 15. Qe5+ { Forcing Black to weaken the kingside by pushing ...f6. }
15... Kg8 { This is quite careless. White can now launch a deadly attack. } 16.
Bxa6
{ This capture is important to understand before going for the attack. Simply put - Black's knight on a6 is completely out of place and will not be able to kick the queen with ...Nd7 and act as a defender with ...Nf6. }
16... Nxa6 17. g4 { Time for action. } 17... hxg4 18. h5 g5 19. Qxg5+ Kh7 20.
Qxg4
{ White maintains a massive attack along the g-file. The material is also equal. Therefore, White's attack will be decisive. }
