{ 4...e6  This is also possible.  5.e4  d5  6.Nb5  directly transposing into the variations with 4... d5. }
5. e4 { We will push the pawn anyways for the sake of active play. } 5... dxe4
{ Capturing the pawn seems most logical. } 6. fxe4
{ Black should be careful here to not take the bait with ...Nxe4. } 6... e6
{ This is the best try. At the moment of writing, this position has 0 games in the database. Therefore, chances of this happening are very slim. }
7. Bd3
{ I would recommend this for 1 or 2 games, if Black finds the right setup, then the position does not seem appealing. }
7... Bb4 8. Qf3 { Protecting the e4-pawn. } 8... c5 9. dxc5 Bxc5
{ This donates the advantage since White can castle on the queenside safely. }
10. O-O-O O-O 11. Qh3
{ Threatening e5 next. White should be completely winning. } *

