{ In this variation, we will once again deny the QID structure. My recommendation is 4. Qf3. This move might seem a bit odd at first, but it has a useful idea. By going Qf3, we are provoking either ...d5 or ...Nc6 and in both cases, Black deviates from QID. if Black goes ...d5 then we can play Nc3-O-O-O and attack on the kingside via g4-g5. If Black plays ...Nc6 then once again we will continue with Nc3-O-O-O and continue with e4 with the idea of breaking through via d5. }
