6. h3 Nbd7 7. Bh2
{ Safely tucking the bishop away. We are deviating from mainstream theory with castling, but once again - it will eventually transpose into the mainline when we castle. Black has three ideas in this position. 1@@EndBracket@@  7...c5  2@@EndBracket@@  7...Qe8  or 3@@EndBracket@@  7...Re8  with the idea of ...e5. }
7... c5
{ Most popular move. Black's idea is to either go for ...Qb6 or follow the normal plan with ...b6-Bb7. }
8. O-O
{ Generally, we would respond with c3. In this case, after  8.c3  Black has an extra possibility of  8...b5!?  and this is why I prefer to play 8. O-O instead. }
8... b6 9. a4 Bb7 10. c3 { Better late than never! } 10... a6 11. Re1 Ra7
