9. Nc3 a6 { Is slightly worse. } 10. cxb5 axb5 11. Bxb5 Bg7 12. Nc4
{ Kicking the queen away. } 12... Qa7 { Only move. } 13. h4
{ 13.O-O  is also fine, but I think including h4-h5 makes Black's position slightly more exposed, which gives White better chances of attack in the future. }
13... O-O { Is a bit optimistic. } 14. h5 e6
{ 14...Na6  can simply be met with  15.h6  Bh8  16.O-O±  and we have achieved what we wanted. The pawn on h6 will play a crucial role in any type of kingside attack in the future. }
15. Be5 Bxd5
{ 15...Nxd5  blunders immediately,  16.Bxg7  Kxg7  17.Nxd5  Bxd5  18.h6+  Kg8  19.Qf6+-  with a mate to follow. }
16. Qf4 Nxh5 { Only move once again. } 17. Rxh5 gxh5
{ Allows a forced sequence. } 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Qg5+ Kh8 20. Qf6+ Kg8 21. Nxd5
exd5 22. O-O-O { And White will mate in a few moves. } *

