3... b5
{ Is liked by the computer most. But I feel that practically this is not the best decision as Black ends up in sharp positions where precise play is required. }
4. e4
{ At the time of writing, this move only has 3 games where White has scored 2.5. Black needs to play extremely precisely in order to not end up in a worse position. }
4... Nxe4
{ The only realistic response.  4...Bb7  for example, immediately gives White a substantial advantage after  5.Bxb5  Nxe4  6.Ne2±  White is clearly better thanks to piece activity. The follow-up should be to go castle and Nbc3. }
5. Qf3
{ Kicking the knight away and aiming to take the b5-pawn.  5.Bxb5??  allowas  5...Qa5+-+ }
