{ 16...Rhf8?  allows  17.Re1!  Rde8  18.Re6!+-  followed by Qe1 and Black is in big trouble. }
17. Rf3 c4
{ Black smartly protects the a3-square, but also creates a target on the queenside. }
18. Be3
{ With a great position. White should take the a7-pawn at the first opportunity and perhaps go for Bd4 at some stage as well. Black's king will not be safe anytime soon, and the Queen on a6 seems to be having a pointless game so far. }
