15. Bf4 { Clever move aimed against ... N8d7. } 15... Qe7 16. h4
{ Protecting the g5-pawn so Bxd6 becomes a real threat, as well as gaining space on the kingside and creating attacking chances via h5-h6. }
16... N8d7 17. dxe6 Qxe6 18. Bxd6 Rfc8 19. Bf4
{ With the idea of h5-Qf3-Nd5 and h6 or g6 at the right moment, White is simply dominating. }
