[White "16) Other First Moves Sidelines"]
[Black "1...e5, the Englund Gambit #4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 e5
{ The Englund Gambit. If your opponent plays this, it is confirmed that they hate the London. So, mission already accomplished! }
2. dxe5 Nc6 3. Nf3 { Simply protecting the pawn. } 3... Qe7 4. Nc3
{ It is possible to save the pawn with  4.Bf4  . But I feel this is much easier to gain an advantage. }
4... Nxe5 { Black recovers the pawn. } 5. Bf4 Nxf3+
{ 5...d6  does not change much since White can go  6.Qd4+-  and provoke ...Nxf3. }
6. gxf3
{ White is already way ahead in development. The idea is to go Qd2 and O-O-O. Black's king will struggle to decide which side to castle as both seem equally dangerous. }
