1. d4 b6
{ The Owen's Defense. This is another dubious setup for White that can simply be punished by taking control of the center. }
2. e4
{ 2.Bf4  This is also possible, I believe the majority of the lines will transpose into QID chapter. For example, if Black goes  2...Bb7  3.Nc3  Nf6  4.f3  is a direct transposition. But if our opponent is giving us the center... why not take it? }
2... Bb7 3. Bd3
{ This move is relatively important to understand. White delays Nc3 on purpose so that Black is unable to go ...e6 and ...Bb4. }
3... e6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e5 { Logical. } 5... Ne4 6. Qe2
{ Challengin the e4-knight. } 6... d5
{ We have reached a position similar to the French Advance where things have gone terribly wrong for Black. }
7. O-O
{ With the idea of going c4 next. Another idea is to play Ne1 followed by f3. One of them should guarantee a winning advantage. }
