[SetUp "1"]

{ Black is threatening to play ...Ba6 and exchange the light-squared bishop. How can White make this idea unsound? }
8. a4 Ba6 9. Bb5
{ Brilliant yet simple. The bishop on a6 remains passive and the knight on b8 will not be getting out anytime soon. If Black takes  9...Bxb5  then  10.axb5  would not only grant a semi-open file but also blocks the b8-knight from coming into play. }
