[SetUp "1"]

{ Black seems to have completely equalized in this position. However, I quite like how Nihal took advantage from here. Simply put, Black's intention is to play ...e5 as soon as possible to gain central control. How did White prepare for this? }
10. Be2
{ Extremely clever move.  10.Bd3  seems a lot more active at first, but when we think of the ...e5 breakthrough, the bishop on d3 is rather misplaced. The bishop on e2, however, can eventually go to f3 where it can put pressure on the d5-pawn. }
10... O-O 11. O-O e5 { Black falls for the trick! } 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5
{ 13.c4⩲  was perhaps even stronger. } 13... Qxe5 14. Bf3
{ With the idea of Qb3-Rd1-Rd2-Rd1. Black has to defend this pawn for a very long time in order to survive. }
