[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Ideas "]
[Black "Kamsky, Gata vs. Nevednichy, Vladislav, 2021"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2q1rk1/1b1nbppp/pp2pn2/2pp4/P2P1B2/2PBPN1P/1P1N1PP1/R2Q1RK1 w - - 0 11"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White's pieces are actively placed. A move like Ne5 seems natural, but it runs the risk of simplifying matters. How should White continue? }
11. Qb1
{ This idea is becoming more and more popular lately. The point is to push b4 and expand on the queenside. }
11... h6 12. b4 cxb4
{ 12...c4?  Eliminates play on the queenside completely for Black.  13.Bc2±  And White has free play on the kingside. The follow-up should be to go Ne5. }
13. cxb4 Rc8 14. Qb2
{ And White is clearly better since the c-file is now completely open. White should try to bring one of the knights to d3 and push a5 to get control of the c5-square. The London Bishop will pose problems for a longtime along the h2-b8 diagonal. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
