[SetUp "1"]

{ Judging by previous examples, it is clear that White should be pushing a5 immediately and break with c4. However, in this case, we can opt for a similar idea which is much better. Can you find it? }
13. c4
{ But wait, why are we switching the move order here? Well, this is because the queen is now placed on c7, preventing Black from breaking the position with ...d5. Therefore, White can be slower and prepare for the eventual a5 break. }
13... Rfe8 14. a5
{ Black is unable to play ...b5. This is why going with c4 is better in this case. }
14... bxa5 15. Qa4 Bc6 16. Qxa5 Qb7 17. b4
{ And White maintains dominance on the queenside. } *

