[SetUp "1"]

{ White has done all the right things. However, Black's bishop on e7 is passive and ...b6 is a bit slow. Both of these moves have one thing in common: the e5-square is completely unchallenged. White to play. }
8. Ne5
{ Taking control over the e5-square and preparing for a potential kingside attack. }
8... Bb7 9. Qf3
{ Shifting the queen to the kingside while keeping control of the e4-square. }
9... Nbd7 10. Rd1 { A bit unnecessary, but White is in no rush. } 10... Rc8 11.
Qh3 Re8 12. Ndf3 { Bringing the knight into action. } 12... g6
{ Black collapses under pressure. } 13. Nxf7
{ Followed by Ng5+. Black resigned here. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
