[SetUp "1"]

{ In many London positions, having a different minor piece compared to your opponent seems to favour White. Therefore, it should be quite clear that the g6-bishop should be targeted. The real question is, should White go Nh4 or Ne5? }
10. Nh4
{ Forcing.  10.Ne5?  generally works, but in this case is a bad move because of  10...Nxe5  11.Bxe5  c4=  Stopping Bb5 ideas and preparing to kick the e5-bishop with ...Nd7. }
10... Be7 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Be2
{ Keeping the idea of h4 alive should Black castle on the kingside. The g6-bishop is eliminated. Black's pieces do not seem as active anymore. I feel that Black should be precise in these situations to keep the game alive, and more often than not - this is where a big mistake happens.   12.Bg2  happened in the game. }
