[SetUp "1"]

{ White has two choices: 1@@EndBracket@@  11.Nxd7  2@@EndBracket@@  11.Nxc6  . One gives a lasting advantage, and the other equalizes. White to play. }
11. Nxd7
{ 11.Nxc6  Seems logical at first.  11...Bxc6  12.Nf3  And now Black can create queenside play via  12...b5⇆ }
11... Qxd7 12. Nf3 { Keeping control of the b5-square. } 12... e6 13. Qb3 Qe7
14. Rfd1 c4 15. Qc2
{ With a slightly better position. I will strongly advise against e4 for now since it opens up the b7-bishop. However, with moves like Nd2 prior, it is possible. }
