[SetUp "1"]

{ White's queen is awkwardly placed. The pawns on e5 and c3 are under attack. How should White continue? }
14. Qa4+ { Aiming to route the queen to d4 where it can protect both. } 14...
Bd7
{ Black makes the most natural move and misses an important resource. Can you find it?   14...Kf8!  was the best continuation.  15.Qd4∞  And the position remains double-edged. }
15. Bb5 Bxb5 16. Qxb5+ Qd7
{ If Black played ...Kf8 then Qxd5 would simply be better. } 17. Qxd7+ Kxd7 18.
Ra5
{ With a great position. The pawn on c3 is no longer a weakness as Black does not have enough resources to attack. The idea should be to double up on the a-file via Nf3-Kd2 and Rfa1. }
