[SetUp "1"]

{ Black's pieces are quite advanced. In particular, the bishop on d3 seems to pose problems. The direct threat is to play ...Bxb1 and capture the pawn on c3. Can you find a way to turn things around? }
17. Ne5 Bxb1 18. cxb4
{ The point. Now Black can only save the bishop or the threat of Nd7. } 18...
Rc2 19. Qxb1 Rxe2 20. Nd7
{ Winning the exchange. The position is still perhaps not completely winning because of Black's active pieces, but it is only a matter of time. The way to play in such positions is to simply exchange the active pieces of your opponent, starting with the rook on e2. }
